A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Prince Hall Freemasonry and the Most Worshipful Prince
2 Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Prince Hall Freemasonry, founded in 1784, in Boston, Massachusetts, has a
4 long and distinguished history of promoting leadership, education, community service, and
5 social justice, serving as a pillar of strength and upliftment within African American
6 communities; and
7 WHEREAS, the Most Worshipful Prince Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia was formed on June
8 24, 1870, in the City of Savannah, Georgia, under the leadership of Grand Master James R.
9 Simms, along with three lodges, Eureka No. 1, Hilton No. 2, and Banneker No. 3; and
10 WHEREAS, the Most Worshipful Prince Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia, together with its 181
11 constituent lodges and over 5,000 members statewide, has awarded more than $100,000 in
12 scholarships to deserving students over the past five years; and
13 WHEREAS, in 2024, the Most Worshipful Prince Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia collectively
14 dedicated over 20,000 hours to community service by collaborating with established
