15 organizations and causes, feeding and clothing the less fortunate, and providing vital youth
16 mentoring services; and
17 WHEREAS, the Most Worshipful Prince Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia has upheld the
18 Masonic principles of brotherly love, relief, and truth, contributing to the spiritual, moral, and
19 civic development of its members and the greater community; and
20 WHEREAS, for generations, Prince Hall Masons have demonstrated an unwavering
21 commitment to philanthropy, youth mentorship, scholarship programs, and public service,
22 including partnerships with local organizations to address issues of health, education, and
23 economic empowerment; and
24 WHEREAS, the contributions of Prince Hall Masons to the social fabric of Georgia reflect
25 the enduring legacy of Prince Hall himself, a visionary leader who sought equality, justice,
26 and unity in the face of adversity; and
27 WHEREAS, it is fitting to recognize and honor the invaluable impact of the Most Worshipful
28 Prince Hall Grand Lodge of Georgia and its affiliated bodies, including the Order of the
29 Eastern Star and Masonic Youth Organizations, in shaping a brighter future for all citizens;
30 and
31 WHEREAS, the Prince Hall Order of the Eastern Star, a distinguished and vital organization
32 made up of our Sisters, has long provided a foundation of faith, service, and philanthropy,
33 working to support charitable causes, promote education, and enrich the lives of families
34 throughout our state; and
